### 2.7. Machine-Friendly Design (AI Assistants and LLMs)

- ‚úÖ **Structured data for AI**: Use schema.org markup so AI assistants can understand content
- ‚úÖ **Clear content hierarchy**: Well-structured content helps both humans and AI parse information
- ‚úÖ **Semantic markup**: Use proper HTML5 elements (not just divs) for better machine understanding
- ‚úÖ **Descriptive metadata**: Rich meta descriptions help AI assistants provide accurate summaries
- ‚úÖ **Logical information architecture**: Clear content structure enables AI to navigate and reference content

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Machine-friendly structure with schema.org -->
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Product",
  "name": "Product Name",
  "description": "Clear value proposition"
}
</script>

<main>
  <article>
    <h1>Main Value Proposition</h1>
    <p>Supporting information</p>
  </article>
</main>
```

**Why it matters (2026)**: As AI assistants become primary ways users find information, designing for machine understanding is essential. Well-structured, semantic content helps AI provide accurate answers.

