## 3. ‚ùå DON'T (Anti-patterns)

### 3.1. Structure and Layout Mistakes

- ‚ùå **Cluttered layouts**: Don't pack too much information into limited space
- ‚ùå **No clear hierarchy**: Don't make everything the same size/importance
- ‚ùå **Hidden navigation**: Don't hide important navigation behind hamburger menus on desktop
- ‚ùå **Inconsistent sections**: Don't use random spacing or styling between sections
- ‚ùå **Horizontal scrolling**: Avoid horizontal scroll on mobile (except intentional carousels)

### 3.2. Content Mistakes

- ‚ùå **Vague messaging**: Don't use generic phrases like "We're the best" without proof
- ‚ùå **Jargon overload**: Don't use industry jargon without explanation
- ‚ùå **Feature-focused copy**: Don't list features without explaining benefits
- ‚ùå **Too much text**: Don't create walls of text without breaks
- ‚ùå **Missing value proposition**: Don't make users guess what you offer

```html
<!-- ‚ùå Bad: Vague, feature-focused -->
<section>
  <h1>Our Revolutionary Solution</h1>
  <p>We leverage cutting-edge technology with innovative features.</p>
</section>

<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Clear value proposition -->
<section>
  <h1>Save 10 Hours Per Week on Reporting</h1>
  <p>Our platform generates reports instantly, so you can focus on decisions.</p>
</section>
```

### 3.3. Navigation Mistakes

- ‚ùå **Broken anchor links**: Don't create anchor links that don't scroll smoothly
- ‚ùå **No back-to-top button**: Don't force users to scroll all the way back up on long pages
- ‚ùå **Inconsistent menu**: Don't change navigation structure between pages
- ‚ùå **Hidden important links**: Don't bury important pages in footer only
- ‚ùå **No active states**: Don't forget to highlight current page/section

### 3.4. CTA Mistakes

- ‚ùå **Weak CTA copy**: Don't use generic "Click Here" or "Learn More"
- ‚ùå **Too many CTAs**: Don't overwhelm users with multiple competing actions
- ‚ùå **Hidden CTAs**: Don't make primary action hard to find
- ‚ùå **No urgency or benefit**: Don't use passive language in CTAs
- ‚ùå **Inconsistent CTA styling**: Don't use different styles for same action type

```html
<!-- ‚ùå Bad: Weak, generic CTA -->
<a href="/page">Click Here</a>
<button>Submit</button>

<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Clear, benefit-focused CTA -->
<a href="/signup">Start Free Trial</a>
```

### 3.5. Performance Mistakes

- ‚ùå **Ignoring performance**: Don't ignore performance impact of design decisions
- ‚ùå **Heavy initial load**: Don't load all content immediately on one-page sites
- ‚ùå **Blocking resources**: Don't block rendering with large JavaScript bundles
- ‚ùå **No loading states**: Don't leave users with blank screens during loading

> **Reference**: See [Performance](technical/performance.mdc) for detailed optimization strategies. See [HTML Performance](../../html/html-performance.mdc) for image optimization techniques.

### 3.6. Common Cliches and Overused Patterns

- ‚ùå **Autoplay carousels**: Don't auto-rotate carousels too fast or without user control
- ‚ùå **Stock photo overuse**: Don't use generic stock photos that add no value
- ‚ùå **Gradient banners everywhere**: Don't use gradients just because "everyone does"
- ‚ùå **Oversized hero sliders**: Don't create massive hero sections that push content below fold
- ‚ùå **Page curl effects**: Don't use dated decorative effects like page curls or book metaphors

```html
<!-- ‚ùå Bad: Fast autoplay without control -->
<div data-autoplay="true" data-interval="2000">
  <!-- Slides rotate every 2 seconds -->
</div>

<!-- ‚úÖ Good: User-controlled with pause -->
<div data-autoplay="true" data-interval="5000" data-pause-on-hover="true">
  <button aria-label="Pause">Pause</button>
</div>
```

### 3.7. Dark Patterns and Deceptive Practices

- ‚ùå **Roach motel pattern**: Don't make it easy to sign up but hard to cancel
- ‚ùå **Hidden costs**: Don't reveal additional fees only at checkout
- ‚ùå **Fake urgency**: Don't use fake countdown timers or "only 1 left" without truth
- ‚ùå **Sneaky upsells**: Don't add items to cart without explicit consent
- ‚ùå **Forced registration**: Don't require sign-up before showing value

### 3.8. Privacy by Design and Ethical UX

- ‚úÖ **Transparent data collection**: Clearly explain what data is collected and why
- ‚úÖ **Privacy controls in UI**: Provide easy-to-find privacy settings and data controls
- ‚úÖ **Minimal data collection**: Only collect data that's necessary for functionality
- ‚úÖ **Clear consent**: Use explicit, understandable language for consent requests
- ‚úÖ **Easy opt-out**: Make it as easy to opt-out as it is to opt-in
- ‚úÖ **Explain data usage**: Tell users how their data will be used before collection

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Transparent privacy controls -->
<div>
  <h2>Privacy Settings</h2>
  <p>Control how your data is used:</p>
  
  <label>
    <input type="checkbox" checked>
    <span>Analytics: Share anonymous usage data</span>
    <small>We use this to understand how users interact with our site</small>
  </label>
  
  <button>Save Preferences</button>
  <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy policy</a>
</div>
```

**Why it matters (2026)**: Privacy by Design is becoming a legal requirement. Users expect transparency and control over their data. Ethical UX builds trust.

```html
<!-- ‚ùå Bad: Hidden cost -->
<div>
  <h2>$9.99/month</h2>
  <!-- Hidden: +$2.99 fee shown only at checkout -->
</div>

<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Transparent pricing -->
<div>
  <h2>$9.99/month</h2>
  <p>+ $2.99 processing fee</p>
  <p>Total: $12.98/month</p>
</div>
```

### 3.9. Pop-up and Interruption Mistakes

- ‚ùå **Immediate pop-ups**: Don't show pop-ups before user has time to see content
- ‚ùå **Aggressive pop-ups**: Don't show pop-ups on every page visit
- ‚ùå **Auto-play media**: Don't auto-play videos or audio without user consent
- ‚ùå **Exit-intent abuse**: Don't use exit-intent pop-ups excessively
- ‚ùå **No close button**: Don't make pop-ups hard to dismiss


## 4. üìù Key Points

### 4.1. One-Page Website Checklist

When designing a one-page website, verify:

#### Structure
- [ ] Clear hero section with value proposition
- [ ] Distinct content sections (Features, About, Testimonials, Contact)
- [ ] Sticky navigation with smooth anchor links
- [ ] "Back to top" button for long pages
- [ ] Proper heading hierarchy (one H1, logical H2-H6)

#### Content
- [ ] Compelling headline that communicates value
- [ ] Benefit-focused copy (not just features)
- [ ] Social proof (testimonials, client logos)
- [ ] Clear, specific CTAs (not generic "Click Here")
- [ ] FAQ section if applicable

#### Performance
- [ ] Fast initial load (< 3 seconds on 3G)
- [ ] Smooth scroll behavior for anchor links
- [ ] No blocking JavaScript
- [ ] Optimized assets (images, fonts, scripts)

#### User Experience
- [ ] Works perfectly on mobile devices
- [ ] Clear visual section separators
- [ ] Accessible and usable across devices

#### Conversion
- [ ] Primary CTA in hero section
- [ ] Secondary CTAs at key decision points
- [ ] Contact form or clear contact method
- [ ] Trust elements visible (testimonials, guarantees)
- [ ] Analytics tracking set up

### 4.2. Must Have
- Clear primary goal and value proposition
- Logical content structure with distinct sections
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Fast loading and performance optimization
- Strategic CTA placement
- Social proof and trust elements

### 4.3. Do
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- Implement smooth scroll for anchor navigation
- Test on real devices and screen sizes
- Monitor analytics (scroll depth, bounce rate, conversions)
- Iterate based on user feedback and data
- Follow WCAG 2.2 AA guidelines minimum
- Use proper heading hierarchy (one H1 per page)
- Provide clear visual section separators
- Optimize performance (see [Performance](technical/performance.mdc) for details)

### 4.4. Don't
- Don't create cluttered layouts with no hierarchy
- Don't use vague or jargon-filled messaging
- Don't hide important navigation or CTAs
- Don't auto-play media without consent
- Don't use deceptive patterns (fake urgency, hidden costs)
- Don't show aggressive pop-ups immediately
- Don't ignore mobile users (majority of traffic)
- Don't sacrifice performance for visual effects
- Don't use generic stock photos that add no value
- Don't create "roach motel" experiences (easy in, hard out)

